name: Lunch.js Event
description: Lunch.js Location Event Template
title: "<neighborhood> - <date>"
labels:
  - event

body:
  - type: markdown
    attributes:
      value: |
        Hey Everyone,

        The next Lunch.js Event is Tuesday, 12:30pm:
  - type: input
    id: date
    attributes:
      label: Lunch.JS Date
      description: The next first Tuesday of the month
      placeholder: January 1, 2025
    validations:
      required: true

  - type: input
    id: neighborhood
    attributes:
      label: Neighborhood
      description: The neighborhood of the lunch event (DTLA, Santa Monica, Culver City, etc.)
      placeholder: Santa Monica
    validations:
      required: true

  - type: input
    id: champion
    attributes:
      label: Champion Name(s)
      description: Your Name(s) and Github username(s)
        (e.g., "Angus Perkerson @anguspiv")
      placeholder: "Angus Perkerson @anguspiv"
    validations:
      required: true

  - type: textarea
    id: location
    attributes:
      label: Location
      description: |
        Location of the lunch event (restaurant, park, etc.)
        As the champion you can pick a place, or be really cool and
        make a poll where people can vote on the location!
        Use reaction emojis as to let people vote.
        Including yelp links and addresses is helpful.
        Possible reaction emojis:
        :+1: thumbs up
        :-1: thumbs down
        :smile:
        :tada:
        :confused:
        :heart:
      placeholder: |
        [Santa Monica Pier](https://www.santamonicapier.org/)
        200 Santa Monica Pier
        Santa Monica, CA 90401
        or 
        :+1: [Santa Monica Pier](https://www.santamonicapier.org/)
        :-1: [Santa Monica Beach](https://www.santamonicabeach.org/)
        :heart: [Vitos Pizza](https://www.vitospizza.com/)
    validations:
      required: true

  - type: textarea
    id: description
    attributes:
      label: Description
      description: |
        Provide any additional information about the lunch event, or comments you have.
        Let others know how to identify you at lunch, so new Lunchers won't feel lost!
      placeholder: |
        I'll be the one with purple hair and red glasses

  - type: markdown
    attributes:
      value: |
        If you are planning to attend subscribe to the issue to get notifications for new comments.

  - type: markdown
    attributes:
      value: |
        As a reminder, Lunch.js events follow the [JS.LA Code of Conduct](https://js.la/code-of-conduct).
        Please let your champion know, or reach out to [Angus Perkerson](mailto:angus.perkerson@example.com)
        or any [JS.LA Team Member](https://js.la/team) if you have any questions or concerns.
